-- TAV Buys 35% of Havas From HSBC, Is Girisim for 80 Million Euros
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-08-29T15:07:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-29/tav-buys-35-of-havas-from-hsbc-is-girisim-for-80-million-euros.html
TAV Havalimanlari Holding AS (TAVHL) , a
Turkish airport operator majority-owned by  Aeroports de Paris ,
bought back 35 percent of ground-handler Havaalanlari Yer
Hizmetleri AS from an  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  unit and  Is Girisim
Sermayesi Yatirim Ortakligi AS (ISGSY)  for 80 million euros ($100.2
million).  TAV, which sold the stake to HSBC Investment Bank Holdings
Plc and Is Girisim in 2009 for a total of 102 million euros,
signed an agreement with the sellers today, it said in a filing
with the  Istanbul Stock Exchange . TAV agreed to pay 15.2 million
euros to Is Girisim for its 6.7 percent stake as part of the
deal, Is Girisim said in a separate statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 